## 1. Who We Are

Curio Words is an independent mobile application. If you have questions about this policy, contact us at:

ðŸ“§ rostixter@gmail.com

---

## 2. What Data We Collect

### 2.1 Data We Do NOT Collect

Curio Words does **not** require you to create an account. We do **not** collect:

- Your name, email address, or phone number
- Passwords or login credentials
- Payment information
- Location data

### 2.2 Data collected automatically

We use **Firebase Analytics** (by Google) to help us understand how the app is used. This runs anonymously and may include:

- App launch and session duration
- Which screens you visit
- Anonymous device identifiers (e.g. device model, OS version)

This data is **aggregated and anonymous** â€” we cannot identify you personally from it.

> Firebase Analytics Privacy Policy: https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy

### 2.3 Content Delivery (Supabase)

The app downloads word content (vocabulary words and their descriptions) from our backend powered by **Supabase**. This process does **not** transmit or store any personal information â€” only the word content you see in the app.

> Supabase Privacy Policy: https://supabase.com/privacy

---

## 3. Push Notifications

If you grant permission, we may send you daily word reminders via push notifications. We use **Apple Push Notification Service (APNs)** for this.

- You can withdraw permission at any time in your iPhone's **Settings â†’ Notifications â†’ Curio Words**.
- We do not store your push notification token beyond what is required to deliver notifications on your device.

---

## 4. Data Retention

Since we do not collect personal information, there is nothing personal to delete. Anonymous analytics data is retained by Google Firebase for a maximum of **14 months** per their standard policy.

---

## 5. Children's Privacy

Curio Words is suitable for all ages and does not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 (or the applicable age in your jurisdiction). Since we do not collect personal data from any users, there is no additional risk.

---

